            If opcode is equal to 20615:
                Return 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20301:
                Set loop_terms to loop_terms plus 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20302:
                Set loop_terms to loop_terms plus 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20201:
                Set store_count to store_count plus 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20204:
                Set store_count to store_count plus 1
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If loop_terms is greater than or equal to 1:
        If store_count is greater than or equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
check_relu_pattern recognises ReLU = max(0, x). In MIR with no native max, this
is a compare of x against zero (MIR_GT 20104 or MIR_LT 20102 against a
MIR_CONST 20001 zero) followed by a select/branch that picks x or 0. The
conservative marker is a comparison consuming a constant together with a
branch in a short body.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 for a null sequence. Returns 1 when the sequence contains a constant
(MIR_CONST 20001), a comparison against zero (MIR_GT 20104 or MIR_LT 20102), and
a branch (MIR_BRANCH 20301) - the max(0,x) clamp shape - and contains no
exponential/division marker that would indicate sigmoid/tanh/softmax. Returns 0
otherwise.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) single pass. No allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read; conservative 0 when the clamp shape is absent.
@End Security_Scope

