@Implementation:
Returns 0 for a null sequence. Counts call instructions (MIR_CALL 20304) and
checks for the presence of a division (MIR_DIV 20005) and an addition
(MIR_ADD 20002). Returns 1 when there is exactly one call (one exp) together
with both a division and an addition; 0 otherwise. The single-call requirement
distinguishes sigmoid from softmax, which sums many exp results.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) single pass. No allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read; conservative 0 when the single-exp reciprocal shape is absent.
@End Security_Scope

