End Process

@Reasoning:
check_tanh_pattern recognises tanh activation. Its MIR marker is a single
transcendental call (MIR_CALL 20304 to a tanh/exp intrinsic) combined with a
subtraction and a division (the (e^x - e^-x)/(e^x + e^-x) form reduces to one
call plus sub plus div), with no constant-one addition that would mark sigmoid.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 for a null sequence. Checks for a call (MIR_CALL 20304), a subtraction
(MIR_SUB 20003), and a division (MIR_DIV 20005). Returns 1 when all three are
present; 0 otherwise. The subtraction requirement distinguishes tanh from
sigmoid (which uses an addition of one).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) single pass. No allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read; conservative 0 when the tanh shape is absent.
@End Security_Scope

