@Reasoning:
check_softmax_pattern recognises softmax = exp(x_i) / sum_j(exp(x_j)). Its
distinctive MIR markers are multiple exponential calls (or one exp call inside a
loop) feeding an accumulating sum, followed by a division of each exp by that
sum - so the signature is a loop plus a call plus an accumulating add plus a
division.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 for a null sequence. Detects a loop terminator (MIR_BRANCH 20301 /
MIR_JUMP 20302), at least one call (MIR_CALL 20304, the exp), an addition
(MIR_ADD 20002, the running sum) and a division (MIR_DIV 20005, the
normalisation). Returns 1 when all four markers are present; 0 otherwise. The
loop-plus-sum requirement distinguishes softmax from the single-element sigmoid.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) single pass. No allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read; conservative 0 when the normalised-exponential shape is absent.
@End Security_Scope

